place.name: UP NATELY
place.gazetteerText: NATELY-UP, a parish in Basingstoke district Hants; 1 mile S of Nately-Scures, and 4 E by S of Basingstoke r. station. Post-town, Basingstoke. Acres, 1,013. Real property, £805. Pop., 99. Houses, 26. The living is a vicarage, annexed to the vicarage of Basing, in the diocese of Winchester. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
